==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Castellated
<hw>Cas"tel*la`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>castellatus</ets>, fr. <ets>castellare</ets>. See
<er>Castle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Inclosed within a building;
<as>as, a fountain or cistern <ex>castellated</ex></as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Furnished with turrets and battlements, like a
castle; built in the style of a castle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Castellation</ent>⟦br⟧
